{"title_page": "Pro Evolution Soccer 2010", "text_new": "{{Infobox video game\n| title = Pro Evolution Soccer 2010\n| image = [[File:PES 2010 UK Cover.jpg|250px]]<br>[[United Kingdom|UK]] cover art featuring (from left to right) [[Lionel Messi]] and [[Fernando Torres]]\n| developer = Konami Computer Entertainment Tokyo\n| publisher = [[Konami]]\n| designer = Dhanush Mahendran (executive)<br />Naoya Hatsumi (producer)<br />Toru Nagai (artistic director)<br />Satoshi Suzuki (game mechanics director)<br />Jon Murphy (European team leader)\n| engine =joursaint\n|released = {{collapsible list|title=23 October 2009|'''PS3<ref>{{cite web |title=Pro Evolution Soccer 2010 Release Information for PlayStation 3 |url=http://www.gamefaqs.com/console/ps3/data/959291.html |work=gamefaqs.com |publisher=CBS Interactive Inc. |accessdate=2009-09-25}}</ref> and Xbox 360'''<ref>{{cite web |title=Pro Evolution Soccer 2010 Release Information for Xbox 360 |url=http://www.gamefaqs.com/console/xbox360/data/959290.html |work=gamefaqs.com |publisher=CBS Interactive Inc. |accessdate=2009-09-25}}</ref><br />{{vgrelease|EU|23 October 2009|AUS|29 October 2009}}{{vgrelease|NA|3 November 2009}}{{vgrelease|JP|5 November 2009}}'''PC'''<ref>{{cite web |title=Pro Evolution Soccer 2010 Release Information for PC |url=http://www.gamefaqs.com/computer/doswin/data/959292.html |work=gamefaqs.com |publisher=CBS Interactive Inc. |accessdate=2009-09-25}}</ref><br />{{vgrelease|EU|23 October 2009|AUS|29 October 2009}}{{vgrelease|NA|31 December 2009}}'''PSP'''<ref>{{cite web |title=Pro Evolution Soccer 2010 Release Information for PSP |url=http://www.gamefaqs.com/portable/psp/data/959293.html |work=gamefaqs.com |publisher=CBS Interactive Inc. |accessdate=2009-09-25}}</ref><br />{{vgrelease|EU|6 November 2009}}{{vgrelease|NA|10 November 2009}}'''PS2'''<ref>{{cite web |title=Pro Evolution Soccer 2010 Release Information for PlayStation 2 |url=http://www.gamefaqs.com/console/ps2/data/959294.html |work=gamefaqs.com |publisher=CBS Interactive Inc. |accessdate=2009-09-25}}</ref><br />{{vgrelease|EU|6 November 2009}}{{vgrelease|NA|10 November 2009|AUS|12 November 2009}}'''Wii'''<ref>{{cite web |title=Pro Evolution Soccer 2010 Release Information for Wii |url=http://www.gamefaqs.com/console/wii/data/960815.html |work=gamefaqs.com |publisher=CBS Interactive Inc. |accessdate=2009-09-25}}</ref><br />{{vgrelease|NA|10 November 2009|EU|20 November 2009|AUS|3 December 2009}}}}\n| series = ''[[Pro Evolution Soccer]]''\n| genre = [[Sports game|Sports]]\n| modes = [[Single-player video game|Single-player]], [[Multiplayer video game|Multiplayer]]\n| platforms = [[Microsoft Windows]]<br>[[PlayStation 2]]<br>[[PlayStation 3]]<br>[[PlayStation Portable]]<br>[[Xbox 360]]<br>[[iOS]]<br>[[Wii]]<br>[[Mobile Phone]]\n}}\n\n'''''Pro Evolution Soccer 2010''''' (officially abbreviated as '''''PES 2010''''' and known in Asia as '''''World Soccer: Winning Eleven 2010''''') is the ninth [[Association football|football]] video game in the ''[[Pro Evolution Soccer]]'' series. The game was developed and published by [[Konami]] for release on [[Sony]]'s [[PlayStation 2]], [[PlayStation 3]], and [[PlayStation Portable]]; [[Microsoft]]'s [[Xbox 360]] and [[Microsoft Windows|Windows]]; [[Nintendo]]'s [[Wii]]; and [[mobile phone]]s.<ref name=\"PES 2010\">{{cite web |title=PES 2010: New Season, All New Game |url=http://uk.games.konami-europe.com/news.do?idNews=396 |date=2009-04-08 |work=konami-europe.com |publisher=Konami Digital Entertainment |accessdate=2009-08-24 |url-status=dead |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20090930183546/http://uk.games.konami-europe.com/news.do?idNews=396 |archivedate=2009-09-30 }}</ref>\n\n''PES 2010'' was announced on 8 April 2009<ref name=\"PES 2010\" /> and the playable demo for the PC, PS3, and Xbox 360 versions was released on 17 September 2009.<ref>{{cite web |title=PES 2010 Demo available on XBLA / PSN / PC on September 17th |url=http://winningelevenblog.com/blog/pes2010-demo-available-on-xbla-psn-pc-on-september-17th/ |date=2009-09-16 |work=winningelevenblog.com |publisher=self-published |accessdate=2009-09-16}}</ref> The game itself was released on 23 October 2009 in Europe.\n\n[[Lionel Messi]] ([[FC Barcelona]] and Argentine player) is a key endorsement player for ''PES 2010'', having featured extensively throughout the promotion and development of the game.<ref>{{cite web |title=Messi E3 Trailer + Screenshots |url=http://www.pesfan.com/news/8165753/?widget_konami=1#news |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20090607001806/http://www.pesfan.com/news/8165753/?widget_konami=1#news |url-status=dead |archive-date=2009-06-07 |work=pesfan.com |publisher=PESFan |accessdate=2009-08-24 }}</ref> He features on the cover alongside [[Fernando Torres]] (Spanish and [[Liverpool F.C.]] player), another endorsement player.<ref>{{cite web |title=Torres signs for PES 2010 |url=http://www.videogamer.com/news/torres_signs_for_pes_2010.html |date=2009-06-23 |work=videogamer.com |publisher=Pro-G Media |accessdate=2009-08-24}}</ref> ''PES 2010'' was succeeded by ''[[Pro Evolution Soccer 2011]]''.\n\nThe game was released on the [[iPhone OS]] in June 2010.<ref>http://uk.games.konami-europe.com/mobile/iphoneNews.do?idNews=486</ref>\n\n==Features==\n''PES 2010'' has the following features.<ref name=\"PES 2010\" />\n* ''PES 2010'' contains improved visuals, animations and moves, including live player expressions and movements that will change according to conditions on the field. Animations of dribbling and shots on goal, as well as individual skills, have all been reworked.\n* Gameplay has been made more realistic. This includes more versatile goalkeepers and greater control over penalties in terms of placing and accuracy.\n* There will be an enhanced online experience: a new development team is solely dedicated to improving online play and other aspects, such as downloadable content and more updates.\n* The A.I. has been improved thanks to Teamvision 2.0. Referees have been reworked to make more balanced calls during matches.\n* ''PES 2010'' introduces greater strategy control: various strategic elements, such as pass frequency and width of play, can be altered.\n* The match-day atmosphere gives a better taste of home and away crowds, which will react spontaneously to all the action on the pitch.\n* Master League has been enhanced. It has improved managerial aspects, resulting in an increased managerial career lifespan.\n* 360-degree control is introduced, available on the PC, PS3, and Xbox 360 versions of the game via the analog sticks on the respective controllers. PS3 owners will also benefit from this when using the [[DualShock]]'s D-Pad, but the Wii D-Pad is limited to eight-directional control and the Xbox 360 D-Pad to sixteen-directional control due to their hardware.\n\n==Content==\nWith an exclusive deal with [[UEFA]], both the [[UEFA Champions League]] and (for the first time) the [[UEFA Europa League]] are fully licensed.<ref name=\"PES 2010\" /> The tournaments are integrated into the Master League mode;<ref>{{cite web |title=OPM France Confirms CL Integration |url=http://winningelevenblog.com/blog/opm-france-confirms-cl-intergration/ |date=2009-05-03 |work=winningelevenblog.com |publisher=self-published |accessdate=2009-08-24}}</ref> however, the Europa League is only available on the PC, PS3 and Xbox 360 versions.\n\nDouble Fusion signed an agreement with Konami for advertising their clients products in the game.<ref>{{cite web |title=Double Fusion signs in-game advertising agreement with Konami Digital Entertainment for PES 2010 |url=http://www.doublefusion.com/press/html/Konami_PES_20_04_09.html |date=2009-04-20 |work=doublefusion.com |publisher=Double Fusion |accessdate=2009-08-24}}</ref>\n\nIn total, the game includes 258 squads, with 139 of them being officially licensed. Including the empty league, the game has a total of 55 teams that can be changed completely by user editing.<ref>{{cite web |title=PES 2010: Edit Mode |url=http://www.thesportsgamer.com/?p=447 |date=2009-11-05 |work=thesportsgamer.com |publisher=TSG: The Sports Gamer |accessdate=2009-11-05}}</ref>\n\nLike previous versions, there is also a separate league with 18 empty teams (Team A, Team B, etc.), each of which can be edited fully. This was initially introduced when Konami failed to get the rights to the German [[Fu\u00dfball-Bundesliga|Bundesliga]]. Since its introduction, it has become very popular amongst the ''PES'' community, and as a result, they are usually made into the Bundesliga or another league of one's preference by patch makers. Popular made leagues are the [[Liga Sagres]], [[Belgian First Division A]], [[Football League Championship|Championship]], [[EFL League One]], [[EFL League Two]] [[Liga I]], [[Argentine Primera Divisi\u00f3n]] or [[Primera Divisi\u00f3n de M\u00e9xico]], Greek Superleague and Moroccan Botola Pro.\n\n===Commentators===\n* [[Jon Champion]] and [[Mark Lawrenson]] provide the English commentary.<ref>{{cite web |title=Pjedsikan JES jed 2010 \u2013 England vs Brazil Highlights |url=https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=SQLk5_KLQDc&feature=player_embedded# |date=2009-10-10 |work=youtube.com |publisher=self-published |accessdate=2009-10-16}}</ref>\n* [[Gr\u00e9goire Margotton]] and [[Christophe Dugarry]] provide the French commentary.\n* Wolff-Christoph Fuss and Hansi K\u00fcpper provide the German commentary.\n* [[Jon Kabira]] and [[Tsuyoshi Kitazawa]] provide the Japanese commentary.\n* Carlos Mart\u00ednez and Julio Maldonado provide the Spanish commentary for Spain.\n* Pierluigi Pardo and [[Jos\u00e9 Altafini]] provide the Italian commentary.\n* Pedro Sousa and Lu\u00eds Freitas Lobo provide the Portuguese commentary for Portugal.\n* Christian Martinoli and Luis Garc\u00eda provide the Spanish commentary for Latin America.\n\n==Updates==\n\n===Version 1.01===\nOn 22 October 2009, the first patch for the PC, PS3, and Xbox 360 versions of the game was released between 10:00 and 12:00 (GMT). The \"Legends,\" \"Community,\" and \"Competition\" online modes were added.<ref>{{cite web |title=2009.10.22 New patch file released |url=http://www.maintemgr.konamistyle.jp/mds/2.0/client/web_pes2010/detail.php?os=o&pid=ps3&did=uk&mid=5247 |date=2009-10-22 |work=konamistyle.jp |publisher=Konami Digital Entertainment |accessdate=2009-10-22}}</ref>\n\n===Version 1.02===\nOn 9 November 2009, a patch for ''World Soccer: Winning Eleven 2010'' was released at 6:00 (GMT). The patch updated the Japan national team kits and various team squads.<ref>{{cite web |title=PES 2010 Update Out Thursday? |url=http://winningelevenblog.com/blog/pes-2010-update-out-thursday/ |date=2009-11-07 |work=winningelevenblog.com |publisher=self-published |accessdate=2009-11-17}}</ref> A patch for ''PES 2010'' was released on 17 November 2009, which fixes the problem of edit data reverting to default when content is downloaded.<ref>{{cite web |title=PES 2010 1.02 Update Hits |url=http://winningelevenblog.com/blog/pes-2010-1-02-update-hits/ |date=2009-11-17 |work=winningelevenblog.com |publisher=self-published |accessdate=2009-11-17}}</ref> On 24 November 2009, another patch for ''PES 2010'' was released, including graphical additions and a roster update.<ref>{{cite web |title=PES 2010 Update Launches! |url=http://winningelevenblog.com/blog/pes-2010-update-launches/ |date=2009-11-24 |work=winningelevenblog.com |publisher=self-published |accessdate=2009-11-24}}</ref>\n\n===Version 1.03===\nThe update makes the game's formation settings easier to use, and also adds icons to show the connectivity status of online players. All settings can now be saved and stocked data will be loaded automatically, speeding up play immediately. Likewise, the new connectivity icons will show the user as a grey icon, with green, yellow, and red icons detailing the quality of the opponent's connection, with red being the worse. The update also improves match making between users of the PC-DVD version of the game with different processors.<ref>http://winningelevenblog.com/blog/new-patch-dlc-hits/</ref>\n\n===Version 1.04 & 1.05===\nThe new update was released on 16 February 2010 for PlayStation 3, Xbox 360 and PC. The latest update files brings every club team roster in line with all changes and transfers made up to 15 January. Some player parameters were updated in line with their performance in the first half of the season and a new boot design was included.<ref>{{cite web |url=http://www.pesfan.com/news/8813450/New-PES-2010-DLC-Announced/ |title=Archived copy |accessdate=2010-02-13 |url-status=dead |archiveurl=https://archive.is/20120919083651/http://www.pesfan.com/news/8813450/New-PES-2010-DLC-Announced/ |archivedate=2012-09-19 }}</ref><ref>http://www.maintemgr.konamistyle.jp/mds/2.0/client/web_pes2010/detail.php?os=o&pid=ps3&did=uk&mid=5880</ref> However, when implementing the new Download Contents, all save data created before the update remained with certain Edit Data reverting to default. Player and team data will remain edited, while player registration and formation data will revert to Default. Deleting the Download contents from the system menu will invalidate any save data created after its implementation.<ref>http://www.maintemgr.konamistyle.jp/mds/2.0/client/web_pes2010/detail.php?os=o&pid=ps3&did=uk&mid=5881</ref>\n\nIt was revealed on 17 February 2010 that the new update contained incorrect data, and some players' free kick motion do not appear properly. When any of these players are used in a match, the game may not perform properly, and ''PES'' would like the player to refrain from using these players until the problem is addressed. ''PES'' are currently in preparation for releasing the corrected data, which will address the problem once it is applied to the game, and they would like to ask the player not to remove any game data. They are making every effort to release the corrected data later this week, and the schedule will be announced once fixed. They sincerely apologize for any inconveniences caused by this problem.<ref>http://www.maintemgr.konamistyle.jp/mds/2.0/client/web_pes2010/detail.php?os=o&pid=ps3&did=uk&mid=5898</ref>\n\nOn 19 February 2010, a fixed version of the update was released, concerning the inadequate free kick motion, and included a newer better transfer update.<ref>http://winningelevenblog.com/blog/dlc-fix-released/</ref>\n\n===Version 1.06===\nThe update includes new UEFA Champions League Final Madrid 2010 ball, new ADIDAS F50 Tunit boots and some tweaking to the rosters.<ref>http://winningelevenblog.com/blog/new-pes-2010-dlc-hits/</ref>\n\n===Version 1.07===\nAn update containing various new international kits was released on June 8. It contained updated squads for some international teams, except: Brazil, Argentina, Germany and the Netherlands.\n\n==Reception==\n{{Video game reviews\n| state = collapsed\n<!-- Aggregators -->\n| MC = PS3: 78/100<ref>{{cite web |url=http://www.metacritic.com/game/playstation-3/pro-evolution-soccer-2010 |title=Pro Evolution Soccer 2010 for PlayStation 3 Reviews |work=[[Metacritic]] |publisher=[[CBS Interactive]] |accessdate=2018-08-25}}</ref><br />X360: 78/100<ref>{{cite web |url=http://www.metacritic.com/game/xbox-360/pro-evolution-soccer-2010 |title=Pro Evolution Soccer 2010 for Xbox 360 Reviews |work=[[Metacritic]] |publisher=[[CBS Interactive]] |accessdate=2018-08-25}}</ref><br />PC: 78/100<ref>{{cite web |url=http://www.metacritic.com/game/pc/pro-evolution-soccer-2010 |title=Pro Evolution Soccer 2010 for PC Reviews |work=[[Metacritic]] |publisher=[[CBS Interactive]] |accessdate=2018-08-25}}</ref><br />PSP: 72/100<ref>{{cite web |url=http://www.metacritic.com/game/psp/pro-evolution-soccer-2010 |title=Pro Evolution Soccer 2010 for PSP Reviews |work=[[Metacritic]] |publisher=[[CBS Interactive]] |accessdate=2018-08-25}}</ref><br />WII: 82/100<ref>{{cite web |url=http://www.metacritic.com/game/wii/pro-evolution-soccer-2010 |title=Pro 