{"title_page": "Be aware and share", "text_new": "{{multiple issues|\n{{Story|date=May 2017}}\n{{news release|1=article|date=May 2017}}\n{{fanpov|date=May 2017}}\n{{Orphan|date=May 2017}}\n}}\n'''Be aware and share''' is a [[Switzerland|Swiss]] [[relief organization]] founded in 2015 in the context of the [[European migrant crisis#Triggers of the summer 2015 crisis|European migrant crisis]], and a [[documentary film]] released in 2016.\n\n== The relief organization ==\n\n{{Infobox non-profit\n| Non-profit_name = Be aware and share\n| Non-profit_logo = Be aware and share.png\n| Non-profit_type = relief\n| founded_date = 2015\n| founder = Bastian Seelhofer\n| key_people = Mara Massari (Administration)<br />C\u00e9cile Speitel (Communication)\n| location = [[Frenkendorf]] ([[Switzerland]]), Eggstrasse 19\n| area_served = 2 countries ([[Greece]] and [[Switzerland]])\n| focus = Well being of refugees, especially children.\n| method = Emergency relief, community development and schools for refugee camps.\n| revenue =\n| num_employees = around 20 (2017)\n| Non-profit_slogan = ''Be aware and share / Sei achtsam und teile.''\n| homepage = [http://www.baas-schweiz.ch/index.html www.baas-schweiz.ch]\n}}\n\nThe charity work ''Be aware and share'', portrayed in the film, was founded in [[Basel]] in 2015 by social worker Bastian Seelhofer and colleagues. The operational area of the relief agency is currently [[Switzerland]] and [[Greece]].\n\nWhen the refugee crisis intensified in the summer of 2015, Seelhofer's team decided to transport relief supplies to the [[Drnje|Hungarian-Croatian border]]. In addition, there were deployments for stranded refugees on the Greek island of [[Chios]], a few kilometers from the [[Aegean Region|Turkish Aegean coast]]. There the team of ''Be aware and share'' settled down, Seelhofer resigned his position as a [[youth worker]] in Switzerland and devoted himself henceforth to the humanitarian project.<ref>Michel Schultheiss: [http://www.tageswoche.ch/de/2016_32/basel/726072/%C2%ABWas-sage-ich-einmal-meinem-Sohn-wenn-er-fragt-was-ich-damals-gemacht-habe%C2%BB.htm ''\u00abWas sage ich einmal meinem Sohn, wenn er fragt, was ich damals gemacht habe?\u00bb''] In: ''[[TagesWoche]]'', 6. August 2016.</ref>\n\nIn May 2016, ''Be aware and share'' founded a school in [[Chios]]. The NGO called for the [[UNESCO]] initiative ''[[:de:Education Cannot Wait|Education Cannot Wait]]''. Through donations collected in Switzerland and through voluntary work, she offers several dozen refugee children and young people a structured school day with at least two lessons per day. The teachers, mainly refugees themselves, teach languages (mainly English and native languages of the refugees, for example Arabic) and mathematics, among other things.<ref>[[Robert Trafford]]: [https://www.independent.co.uk/news/world/europe/refugee-school-chios-greece-lessons-in-life-for-the-migrant-children-a7229916.html ''Inside the incredible school teaching refugee children on the Greek island of Chios.''] In: ''[[The Independent]]''. 9 September 2016.</ref> The charity works with other organizations and is financially supported by major relief organizations such as the [[Norwegian Refugee Council]].<ref>Anna Jungen: [http://www.srf.ch/news/regional/basel-baselland/basler-fluechtlingsschule-auf-griechischer-insel-chios ''Basler Fl\u00fcchtlingsschule auf griechischer Insel Chios'']. In: ''[[Schweizer Radio und Fernsehen]]'', [[Radio SRF 1|Regionaljournal Basel]], 7. Juli 2016.</ref>\n\n== The film ==\nThe Swiss-Iranian filmmaker [[Omid Taslimi]], together with [[:de:Lasse Linder|Lasse Linder]], shot a [[documentary film]] about a journey that led ''Be aware and share'' to the Croatian-Hungarian border at [[Drnje|Botovo (Drnje)]] in October 2015. The film shows how the project came about: the collection of clothes at the beginning, the surprise about the great interest in the Swiss population, the founding of the association, a charity concert with [[:de:Collie Herb|Collie Herb]], [[:als:La Nefera|La Nefera]] and other regional musicians. It is reported about the logistical problems and how the team travels by vans to Croatia; It is shown how the Swiss helpers finally find Croatian allies, and together with them, at the border station of [[Botovo, Croatia|Botovo]], give refugees who get off the train and cross the border to [[Hungary]], food and clothes.<ref>Lucas Huber: [http://www.tageswoche.ch/de/2016_7/basel/711051/ \"\u00abBe Aware and Share\u00bb: Ber\u00fchrende Doku \u00fcber junge Basler Fl\u00fcchtlingshelfer\".] In: ''[[TagesWoche]]'', 8. Februar 2016</ref>\n\nApart from situation recordings, the film includes several short interviews with team members, other participants (for example, members of the Bernese aid organization ''Cibera'') and ORF correspondent [[Christian Wehrsch\u00fctz]]. In general, Taslimi focused the film strongly on the motivation of the activists.<ref>Viviane Weber: [http://www.stadtanzeiger-olten.ch/aktuell/im-gespraech/artikelseite-im-gespraech/?tx_ttnews%5Btt_news%5D=82491&cHash=944493c570e06cab89735a471bef813f \"Nicht blockieren, sondern motivieren\".] In: ''[[:de:Stadtanzeiger Olten|Stadtanzeiger Olten]]'', 17. August 2016.</ref> The film was shown in various Swiss [[movie theater]]s.\n\n== External links ==\n\n* {{Helveticat}}\n* {{Official website|www.baas-schweiz.ch/}}\n* {{IMDb title|tt5696588|Be aware and share}}\n* {{Rotten Tomatoes|be_aware_and_share}}\n* [[:de:Thomas Meyer (Schriftsteller)|Thomas Meyer]]: [https://web.archive.org/web/20160927080153/http://thomasmeyer.ch/downloads/Factsheet-Refugees.pdf ''Effektive Fl\u00fcchtlingshilfe vor Ort durch private Schweizer Initiativen''].\n* [http://www.aljazeera.com/indepth/inpictures/2016/07/refugee-school-respite-children-greek-camps-160706184135733.html Photos of the BAAS-School in Chios] on [[Al Jazeera]]\n\n\n== References ==\n{{reflist}}\n\n{{Authority control}}\n\n[[Category:Organizations established in 2015]]\n[[Category:Refugee aid organizations in Europe]]\n[[Category:Children's charities based in Switzerland]]\n[[Category:Organizations established in the 20th century]]\n[[Category:2015 establishments in Switzerland]]\n[[Category:Documentary films about Croatia]]\n[[Category:Documentary films about Switzerland]]\n[[Category:Swiss films]]\n[[Category:Croatian films]]\n[[Category:German-language films]]\n[[Category:Swiss German-language films]]\n[[Category:Croatian-language films]]\n[[Category:English-language films]]\n[[Category:2010s documentary films]]\n[[Category:Croatian documentary films]]\n[[Category:Croatian independent films]]\n[[Category:Swiss documentary films]]\n[[Category:Swiss independent films]]\n[[Category:Documentary films about immigration to Europe]]\n[[Category:Documentary films about refugees]]\n[[Category:Films shot in Croatia]]\n[[Category:Films set in Croatia]]\n", "text_old": "{{multiple issues|\n{{Story|date=May 2017}}\n{{news release|1=article|date=May 2017}}\n{{fanpov|date=May 2017}}\n{{Orphan|date=May 2017}}\n}}\n'''Be aware and share''' is a [[Switzerland|Swiss]] [[relief organization]] founded in 2015 in the context of the [[European migrant crisis#Triggers of the summer 2015 crisis|European migrant crisis]], and a [[documentary film]] released in 2016.\n\n== The relief organization ==\n\n{{Infobox non-profit\n| Non-profit_name = Be aware and share\n| Non-profit_logo = Be aware and share.png\n| Non-profit_type = relief\n| founded_date = 2015\n| founder = Bastian Seelhofer\n| key_people = Mara Massari (Administration)<br />C\u00e9cile Speitel (Communication)\n| location = [[Frenkendorf]] ([[Switzerland]]), Eggstrasse 19\n| area_served = 2 countries ([[Greece]] and [[Switzerland]])\n| focus = Well being of refugees, especially children.\n| method = Emergency relief, community development and schools for refugee camps.\n| revenue =\n| num_employees = around 20 (2017)\n| Non-profit_slogan = ''Be aware and share / Sei achtsam und teile.''\n| homepage = [http://www.baas-schweiz.ch/index.html www.baas-schweiz.ch]\n}}\n\nThe charity work ''Be aware and share'' portrayed in the film was founded in [[Basel]] in 2015 by social worker Bastian Seelhofer and colleagues. The operational area of the relief agency is currently [[Switzerland]] and [[Greece]].\n\nWhen the refugee crisis intensified in the summer of 2015, Seelhofer's team decided to transport relief supplies to the [[Drnje|Hungarian-Croatian border]]. In addition, there were deployments for stranded refugees on the Greek island of [[Chios]], a few kilometers from the [[Aegean Region|Turkish Aegean coast]]. There the team of ''Be aware and share'' settled down, Seelhofer resigned his position as a [[youth worker]] in Switzerland and devoted himself henceforth to the humanitarian project.<ref>Michel Schultheiss: [http://www.tageswoche.ch/de/2016_32/basel/726072/%C2%ABWas-sage-ich-einmal-meinem-Sohn-wenn-er-fragt-was-ich-damals-gemacht-habe%C2%BB.htm ''\u00abWas sage ich einmal meinem Sohn, wenn er fragt, was ich damals gemacht habe?\u00bb''] In: ''[[TagesWoche]]'', 6. August 2016.</ref>\n\nIn May 2016, ''Be aware and share'' founded a school in [[Chios]]. The NGO called for the [[UNESCO]] initiative ''[[:de:Education Cannot Wait|Education Cannot Wait]]''. Through donations collected in Switzerland and through voluntary work, she offers several dozen refugee children and young people a structured school day with at least two lessons per day. The teachers, mainly refugees themselves, teach languages (mainly English and native languages of the refugees, for example Arabic) and mathematics, among other things.<ref>[[Robert Trafford]]: [https://www.independent.co.uk/news/world/europe/refugee-school-chios-greece-lessons-in-life-for-the-migrant-children-a7229916.html ''Inside the incredible school teaching refugee children on the Greek island of Chios.''] In: ''[[The Independent]]''. 9 September 2016.</ref> The charity works with other organizations and is financially supported by major relief organizations such as the [[Norwegian Refugee Council]].<ref>Anna Jungen: [http://www.srf.ch/news/regional/basel-baselland/basler-fluechtlingsschule-auf-griechischer-insel-chios ''Basler Fl\u00fcchtlingsschule auf griechischer Insel Chios'']. In: ''[[Schweizer Radio und Fernsehen]]'', [[Radio SRF 1|Regionaljournal Basel]], 7. Juli 2016.</ref>\n\n== The film ==\nThe Swiss-Iranian filmmaker [[Omid Taslimi]], together with [[:de:Lasse Linder|Lasse Linder]], shot a [[documentary film]] about a journey that led ''Be aware and share'' to the Croatian-Hungarian border at [[Drnje|Botovo (Drnje)]] in October 2015. The film shows how the project came about: the collection of clothes at the beginning, the surprise about the great interest in the Swiss population, the founding of the association, a charity concert with [[:de:Collie Herb|Collie Herb]], [[:als:La Nefera|La Nefera]] and other regional musicians. It is reported about the logistical problems and how the team travels by vans to Croatia; It is shown how the Swiss helpers finally find Croatian allies, and together with them, at the border station of [[Botovo, Croatia|Botovo]], give refugees who get off the train and cross the border to [[Hungary]], food and clothes.<ref>Lucas Huber: [http://www.tageswoche.ch/de/2016_7/basel/711051/ \"\u00abBe Aware and Share\u00bb: Ber\u00fchrende Doku \u00fcber junge Basler Fl\u00fcchtlingshelfer\".] In: ''[[TagesWoche]]'', 8. Februar 2016</ref>\n\nApart from situation recordings, the film includes several short interviews with team members, other participants (for example, members of the Bernese aid organization ''Cibera'') and ORF correspondent [[Christian Wehrsch\u00fctz]]. In general, Taslimi focused the film strongly on the motivation of the activists.<ref>Viviane Weber: [http://www.stadtanzeiger-olten.ch/aktuell/im-gespraech/artikelseite-im-gespraech/?tx_ttnews%5Btt_news%5D=82491&cHash=944493c570e06cab89735a471bef813f \"Nicht blockieren, sondern motivieren\".] In: ''[[:de:Stadtanzeiger Olten|Stadtanzeiger Olten]]'', 17. August 2016.</ref> The film was shown in various Swiss [[movie theater]]s.\n\n== External links ==\n\n* {{Helveticat}}\n* {{Official website|www.baas-schweiz.ch/}}\n* {{IMDb title|tt5696588|Be aware and share}}\n* {{Rotten Tomatoes|be_aware_and_share}}\n* [[:de:Thomas Meyer (Schriftsteller)|Thomas Meyer]]: [https://web.archive.org/web/20160927080153/http://thomasmeyer.ch/downloads/Factsheet-Refugees.pdf ''Effektive Fl\u00fcchtlingshilfe vor Ort durch private Schweizer Initiativen''].\n* [http://www.aljazeera.com/indepth/inpictures/2016/07/refugee-school-respite-children-greek-camps-160706184135733.html Photos of the BAAS-School in Chios] on [[Al Jazeera]]\n\n\n== References ==\n{{reflist}}\n\n{{Authority control}}\n\n[[Category:Organizations established in 2015]]\n[[Category:Refugee aid organizations in Europe]]\n[[Category:Children's charities based in Switzerland]]\n[[Category:Organizations established in the 20th century]]\n[[Category:2015 establishments in Switzerland]]\n[[Category:Documentary films about Croatia]]\n[[Category:Documentary films about Switzerland]]\n[[Category:Swiss films]]\n[[Category:Croatian films]]\n[[Category:German-language films]]\n[[Category:Swiss German-language films]]\n[[Category:Croatian-language films]]\n[[Category:English-language films]]\n[[Category:2010s documentary films]]\n[[Category:Croatian documentary films]]\n[[Category:Croatian independent films]]\n[[Category:Swiss documentary films]]\n[[Category:Swiss independent films]]\n[[Category:Documentary films about immigration to Europe]]\n[[Category:Documentary films about refugees]]\n[[Category:Films shot in Croatia]]\n[[Category:Films set in Croatia]]\n", "name_user": "Zaneyfacts", "label": "safe", "comment": "Just added commas to make it flow", "url_page": "//en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Be_aware_and_share"}
